{"id:": "/div[1]", "tag": "div", "attributes": {"type": "article", "{http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/namespace}id": "MG-1677-08_031", "resp": "mercure"}, "children": [{"id": "/div[1]/head[1]", "tag": "head", "children": [{"id": "/div[1]/head[1]/text()[1]", "text": "Le Solitaire, Sonnet"}]}, {"id": "/div[1]/bibl[1]", "tag": "bibl", "children": [{"id": "/div[1]/bibl[1]/title[1]", "tag": "title", "children": [{"id": "/div[1]/bibl[1]/title[1]/text()[1]", "text": "Le Nouveau Mercure galant"}]}, {"id": "/div[1]/bibl[1]/text()[1]", "text": ", août 1677 (tome VI), p. 31-34."}]}, {"id": "/div[1]/p[1]", "tag": "p", "children": [{"id": "/div[1]/p[1]/text()[1]", "text": "Pendant que les beaux Esprits travaillent pour laisser apres eux dequoy la convaincre des étonnantes merveilles que nous voyons tous les jours, vous voulez bien que nous changions de matiere, & que je vous envoye un Sonnet qui n’est ny sur la Galanterie, ny sur le bonheur de la France, & auquel l’Amour n’a point de part."}]}, {"id": "/div[1]/quote[1]", "tag": "quote", "children": [{"id": "/div[1]/quote[1]/label[1]", "tag": "label", "children": [{"id": "/div[1]/quote[1]/label[1]/text()[1]", "text": "LE SOLITAIRE, "}, {"id": "/div[1]/quote[1]/label[1]/lb[1]", "tag": "lb", "children": []}, {"id": "/div[1]/quote[1]/label[1]/hi[1]", "tag": "hi", "children": [{"id": "/div[1]/quote[1]/label[1]/hi[1]/text()[1]", "text": "Sonnet."}], "attributes": {"rend": "sc"}}]}, {"id": "/div[1]/quote[1]/lg[1]", "tag": "lg", "children": [{"id": "/div[1]/quote[1]/lg[1]/l[1]", "tag": "l", "children": [{"id": "/div[1]/quote[1]/lg[1]/l[1]/text()[1]", "text": "S’eleve qui voudra, par force, ou par adresse,"}], "attributes": {"rend": "i"}}, {"id": "/div[1]/quote[1]/lg[1]/l[2]", "tag": "l", "children": [{"id": "/div[1]/quote[1]/lg[1]/l[2]/text()[1]", "text": "Jusqu’au sommet glissant des grandeurs de la Cour,"}], "attributes": {"rend": "i"}}, {"id": "/div[1]/quote[1]/lg[1]/l[3]", "tag": "l", "children": [{"id": "/div[1]/quote[1]/lg[1]/l[3]/text()[1]", "text": "Je prétens, sans quitter mon aimable sejour,"}], "attributes": {"rend": "i"}}, {"id": "/div[1]/quote[1]/lg[1]/l[4]", "tag": "l", "children": [{"id": "/div[1]/quote[1]/lg[1]/l[4]/text()[1]", "text": "Loin du Peuple & du bruit, rechercher la Sagesse."}], "attributes": {"rend": "i"}}]}, {"id": "/div[1]/quote[1]/ab[1]", "tag": "ab", "children": [{"id": "/div[1]/quote[1]/ab[1]/text()[1]", "text": "***"}], "attributes": {"type": "ornament"}}, {"id": "/div[1]/quote[1]/lg[2]", "tag": "lg", "children": [{"id": "/div[1]/quote[1]/lg[2]/l[1]", "tag": "l", "children": [{"id": "/div[1]/quote[1]/lg[2]/l[1]/text()[1]", "text": "Là sans crainte des Grands, sans faste & sans tristesse,"}, {"id": "/div[1]/quote[1]/lg[2]/l[1]/note[1]", "tag": "note", "children": [{"id": "/div[1]/quote[1]/lg[2]/l[1]/note[1]/text()[1]", "text": "Dans le volume le vers suivant est manquant. Il est précisé dans l'encart « Au Lecteur », au début du tome : « La seconde faute, est le deuxième Vers oublié du second Quatrain du Sonnet du Solitaire, Page 32, où il faut lire apres le cinquiéme Vers du Sonnet, "}, {"id": "/div[1]/quote[1]/lg[2]/l[1]/note[1]/hi[1]", "tag": "hi", "children": [{"id": "/div[1]/quote[1]/lg[2]/l[1]/note[1]/hi[1]/text()[1]", "text": "Mes yeux apres la nuit verront naistre le jour"}], "attributes": {"rend": "i"}}, {"id": "/div[1]/quote[1]/lg[2]/l[1]/note[1]/text()[2]", "text": ". » Nous l’avons ajouté entre crochets."}], "attributes": {"resp": "editor"}}], "attributes": {"rend": "i"}}, {"id": "/div[1]/quote[1]/lg[2]/l[2]", "tag": "l", "children": [{"id": "/div[1]/quote[1]/lg[2]/l[2]/text()[1]", "text": "["}, {"id": "/div[1]/quote[1]/lg[2]/l[2]/hi[1]", "tag": "hi", "children": [{"id": "/div[1]/quote[1]/lg[2]/l[2]/hi[1]/text()[1]", "text": "Mes yeux apres la nuit verront naistre le jour."}], "attributes": {"rend": "i"}}, {"id": "/div[1]/quote[1]/lg[2]/l[2]/text()[2]", "text": "]"}]}, {"id": "/div[1]/quote[1]/lg[2]/l[3]", "tag": "l", "children": [{"id": "/div[1]/quote[1]/lg[2]/l[3]/text()[1]", "text": "Je verray les Saisons se suivre tour-à-tour,"}], "attributes": {"rend": "i"}}, {"id": "/div[1]/quote[1]/lg[2]/l[4]", "tag": "l", "children": [{"id": "/div[1]/quote[1]/lg[2]/l[4]/text()[1]", "text": "Et dans un doux repos j’attendray la Vieillesse."}], "attributes": {"rend": "i"}}]}, {"id": "/div[1]/quote[1]/ab[2]", "tag": "ab", "children": [{"id": "/div[1]/quote[1]/ab[2]/text()[1]", "text": "***"}], "attributes": {"type": "ornament"}}, {"id": "/div[1]/quote[1]/lg[3]", "tag": "lg", "children": [{"id": "/div[1]/quote[1]/lg[3]/l[1]", "tag": "l", "children": [{"id": "/div[1]/quote[1]/lg[3]/l[1]/text()[1]", "text": "Ainsi lors que la Mort viendra rompre le cours"}], "attributes": {"rend": "i"}}, {"id": "/div[1]/quote[1]/lg[3]/l[2]", "tag": "l", "children": [{"id": "/div[1]/quote[1]/lg[3]/l[2]/text()[1]", "text": "Des bienheureux momens qui composent mes jours,"}], "attributes": {"rend": "i"}}, {"id": "/div[1]/quote[1]/lg[3]/l[3]", "tag": "l", "children": [{"id": "/div[1]/quote[1]/lg[3]/l[3]/text()[1]", "text": "Je mourray chargé d’ans, inconnu, solitaire."}], "attributes": {"rend": "i"}}]}, {"id": "/div[1]/quote[1]/ab[3]", "tag": "ab", "children": [{"id": "/div[1]/quote[1]/ab[3]/text()[1]", "text": "***"}], "attributes": {"type": "ornament"}}, {"id": "/div[1]/quote[1]/lg[4]", "tag": "lg", "children": [{"id": "/div[1]/quote[1]/lg[4]/l[1]", "tag": "l", "children": [{"id": "/div[1]/quote[1]/lg[4]/l[1]/text()[1]", "text": "Qu’un Homme est malheureux à l’heure du trépas,"}], "attributes": {"rend": "i"}}, {"id": "/div[1]/quote[1]/lg[4]/l[2]", "tag": "l", "children": [{"id": "/div[1]/quote[1]/lg[4]/l[2]/text()[1]", "text": "Lors qu’ayant negligé le seul bien necessaire,"}], "attributes": {"rend": "i"}}, {"id": "/div[1]/quote[1]/lg[4]/l[3]", "tag": "l", "children": [{"id": "/div[1]/quote[1]/lg[4]/l[3]/text()[1]", "text": "Il meurt connu de tous, & ne se connoist pas !"}], "attributes": {"rend": "i"}}]}]}, {"id": "/div[1]/p[2]", "tag": "p", "children": [{"id": "/div[1]/p[2]/text()[1]", "text": "Ces choses sont belles à dire, mais l’execution en est difficile, & la plûpart de ceux qui font ces sortes d’Ouvrages, songent bien moins à quiter le monde, qu’à faire paroistre leur esprit."}]}]}